author: PrimeOrigin
body: As a well traveled American, I agree with your short term synopsys and see some inertia for our economy and industries in the next few years. Regardless of the outcome I think those educated groups with means will, if not deliberately searching, be very open to opportunities to emigrate. Anticipating a brain drain coupled with the effects of protectionist policies and epic growth elsewhere will land the country in similar conditions in roughly a decade - a young Musk of my generation would likely stay in Canada or go to Germany/Korea.
